{
  "texts": [
    "All studies that used the OULAD dataset extracted learning behavioral/activity features.",
    "Aljohani et al (2019); Huang et al (2022); Liu et al (2022c, 2023); Waheed et al (2022) have only used learning behavioral/activity features; Poudyal et al (2022); Waheed et al (2019); Xie (2021) have added to them demographic features; while Jiao (2022) has used current student's academic performance in addition to learning behavioral/activity features; Al-Zawqari et al (2022); He et al (2020); Song et al (2020); Yang and Bai (2022) have used academic performance features along with demographic and learning behavioral/activity features.",
    "In addition to the DL techniques applied and the features selected, the model's prediction accuracy can be based on many factors, including the volume and type of dataset that is used in training and testing.",
    "The Use of various datasets has led to achieving remarkable prediction accuracy.",
    "As shown in Figure 12, the prediction accuracy of models that used datasets from MOOCs platforms was between 61% and 97.5%, with an average of 86.89%."
  ]
}